Synopsis:
   $pipe(<command>)

Description:
   Executes the given <command> using /EXEC and returns its output.

Returns:
   Output from /EXEC <command>. All new-line characters are stripped.

History:
   This is the same function that is distributed with EPIC, but has
   been modified to use $rand() to generate a unique process name
   rather than using a global variable that is incremented after
   every call. It was written by Jeremy Nelson <jnelson@epicsol.org>.

See Also:
   pipe(6)

